The '''São Tomé shorttail''' ('''''Motacilla bocagii'''''), also known as '''Bocage's longbill''', is a species of [[passerine]] [[bird]] in the family [[Motacillidae]]. It has been classified as the sole member of the genus ''Amaurocichla'', but a 2015 phylogenetic study placed it among the [[Wagtail|wagtails]] in the genus ''Motacilla''.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Per Alström |author2=Knud A. Jønsson |author3=Jon Fjeldså |author4=Anders Ödeen |author5=Per G. P. Ericson |author6=Martin Irestedt |title=Dramatic niche shifts and morphological change in two insular bird species|journal=[[Royal Society Open Science]]|year=2015|volume=2|issue=3|doi=10.1098/rsos.140364|doi-access=free|pmc=4448822|pmid=26064613|article-number=140364|bibcode=2015RSOS....240364A}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author1=Rebecca B. Harris |author2=Per Alström |author3=Anders Ödeen |author4=Adam D. Leaché |title=Discordance between genomic divergence and phenotypic variation in a rapidly evolving avian genus (Motacilla)|journal=[[Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution]]|year=2018|volume=120|pages=183–195|doi=10.1016/j.ympev.2017.11.020|pmid=29246816|arxiv=1707.03864|s2cid=3592799 }}</ref> It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the central and southern parts of the [[São Tomé Island|island of São Tomé]].<ref name="IUCN"/> Its natural [[habitat]] is [[subtropical]] or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s. This species has a small population and is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

